\begin_layout Standard
Note that the above time evolution equations are cast into a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

conservative
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 form, to conserve rest mass and so that shocks may be reliably modeled via a high-resolution shock capturing scheme. Also, to ensure the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

no-monopole
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\nabla \times \ve{B}=0$
\end_inset

 constraint is satisifed, we choose to rewrite the magnetic induction equation in terms of the the vector potential 
\begin_inset Formula $A^{\mu}$
\end_inset

, which is defined so that 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
beq
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Bi=
